    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="505"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d505">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.142/3335e</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Moscow</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PDC1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Poole</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 7, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>22. For <persName corresp="#p_RLCR1">Robins</persName>: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>15158–10095.<note n="1" xml:id="d505fn1">These are Red Cross serial
                                numbers. On the file copy of the telegram is also noted: “Sent at
                                request of American National Red Cross.”</note> Under all
                            circumstances consider desirable that you come home for consultation. We
                            are very reluctant, however, to withdraw entire Red Cross Commission,
                            anticipating that there will be many opportunities to help distribution
                            food and other Red Cross relief measures next two months. Must leave
                            decision in your <pb facs="0598" n="524" xml:id="pg_524"/> hands, for
                            you alone can judge possibilities of personal welfare members
                            commission, also likelihood continuing service, but all here feel that
                            Red Cross will find much valuable relief work to do and hope you before
                            leaving will find possible arrange for sufficient personnel to remain
                            and if you desire we will endeavor send other Red Cross representatives
                            to help in maintaining Red Cross efforts. Position in Russia founded on
                            fine basis already established. Cable promptly. <persName
                                corresp="#p_DHP1">Davison</persName>.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
